com.davidbracewell.hermes

Interface AnnotationSet

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<Annotation>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultAnnotationSet

    public interface AnnotationSet
extends Iterable<Annotation>

    An AnnotationSet acts as the storage mechanism for annotations associated with a document. It provides methods for adding, removing, and navigating the annotations. In particular, a AnnotationSet defines sequential methods of accessing annotations (next(Annotation, AnnotationType), previous(Annotation, AnnotationType)), based on criteria select(Predicate) and select(Span, Predicate), and by id get(long).

    Annotation sets also keep track of completed annotation types, i.e. those processed using a Pipeline. This allows the pipeline to ignore further attempts to annotate a type that is marked complete. In addition to being marked complete, information about the annotator is stored.

    Author:
    David B. Bracewell
